Title:
Heart Disease Analysis using Tableau

Abstract
Heart disease is a major global health concern. This project uses Tableau visualization techniques to analyze healthcare data and identify important risk factors associated with heart disease.

The project examines patient demographics, medical conditions, and lifestyle factors to discover hidden patterns and trends.

Problem Statement
Healthcare organizations generate large amounts of patient data. Extracting useful insights from this data is challenging without proper visualization tools. This project solves the problem by creating interactive Tableau dashboards.

Methodology
Data Collection
Data Cleaning
Data Analysis
Dashboard Creation
Insight Generation
Results

The analysis identifies important relationships between:

Age and heart disease
Cholesterol and disease risk
BMI and health condition
Smoking habits and heart problems

Conclusion
Tableau provides an effective platform for analyzing healthcare data and supporting preventive healthcare decisions.
